//GOD1PRF:815384 Remark 1. The kernel of the homomorphism $v$ consists of all polynomials $f$ such that $f\left(u_{1}, \ldots, u_{n}\right)=0$, i.e., of all families of elements $\left(a_{r_{1} \ldots r_{n}}\right)$ of K , almost all zero, such that
