//GOD1PRF:821121 and since K is an integral domain it follows that the zeros of $f$ in K , other than $a$, are the zeros of $g$. Since $g$ is of degree $n-1$, it has at most $n-1$ zeros in K by the inductive hypothesis, and so $f$ has at most $n$ zeros in K .
